The paper is about a neural language model that incorporates mechanisms for selecting and copying facts from a knowledge graph, which is a common topic in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper deals with information retrieval and knowledge representation, which are relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval) and cs.DB (Databases).
